HEADWORD: Protester
<hw>Pro*test"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who protests; one who utters a solemn declaration.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who protests a bill of
exchange, or note.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protestingly</ent>⟦br⟧
